The Cambodia Peace Conference was not really a crisis. Even though some fighting between Vietnam and Cambodia continued after the conference, it was not caused by the conference. The primary outcome of the conference was the withdrawal of Vietnamese troops from Cambodia.

Neither the U.S. nor USSR sided against India in this conflict. Even though the U.S. normally supported Pakistan in the Cold War, in this particular conflict, they were more concerned with Pakistan's threat to use nuclear weapons and took a stance against Pakistan. The USSR continued to provide India with political and military support.
The U.S. led the coalition against Iraq
A group of over 30 countries around the world formed a coalition against Iraq, which is why so many countries are sided against Iraq.
Jordan and Yemen expressed support for Iraq, but did not play a role in the war, so they are not listed as actors
The countries against Iraq on rows 22-40 had a very minor role in the war, but they are still sent some troops/supplies to support the coalition.
Germany, Luxembourg, Japan were also part of the coalition. However, they had almost no role in the war so they are not listed as actors

France and Belgium weren't fighting against the government of Zaire but rather against rebellious military troops. For the purpose of coding, this group of military troops is considered to represent Zaire.
The conflict was initiated when the region of Nargonyy Karabakh declared independence. Since this region consisted mostly of Armenians, Armenia is considered to initate the conflict.
The dispute was not resolved, but Egypt was able to successfully annex the Halaib triangle, so they have been considered to win the dispute.

In particular, it was Serbs vs. Bosnians, but Serbia was a part of Yugoslavia at the time, so it is coded as Yugoslavia. Bosnia declared independence, so they are coded as the initiators, but it was Yugoslavia that first responded with military force.

Croatia was initially allianced with Bosnia and helped fight against Yugoslavia. Over time, Croatia and Bosnia began fighting with each other, which is why Croatia is coded on both sides. It is not very clear who initiated the conflict.
The main conflict was between Papa New Guinea and Bougainville, an autonomous region. Since Bougainville is not listed as a state, this dyad is not included.
This war was primarily an instrastate conflict since it occurred between the Burma government and the Karen people, an ethnic group in Burma. Thailand troops were still involved.
Rwanda and Uganda initially fought together but then turned against each other
The other countries supporting DRC did not really come into conflict with Burundi, since Burundi only had a small role in the war.

The bombings were initiated by al Qaeda. Since al Qaeda is based in Afghanistan, it is coded as Afghanistan. Sudan not included as an actor because Sudan got bombed but didn't make any threats in return
Iraq is considered to win since at the end, United Nations troops were withdrawn from Iraq
This conflict was mainly between Yugoslavia and the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA). The KLA was a Kosovo Albanian militia and is coded as Albania.
A group of 10 countries from NATO was involved in bombings against Yugoslavia. This group was led by the United States. All 10 countries have been listed as individual actors.
Both countries made military threats to each other. Pakistan initally invaded and India responded back with a larger force.
A large task force called INTERFET opposed Indonesia in this conflict. This coalition was led by Australia and included 19 other countries.
In addition to Australia, New Zealand and Thailand played non-negligible roles in the conflict. The other countries in the coalition were minimally involved and are not included as actors.
The U.S./U.K. are considered to lose since the Taliban regained control in 2021

Not really a conflict. The Myanmar government was fighting against the Shan and Karen ethnic groups within Mynamar. Myanmar accused Thailand of supporting these ethnic groups, but Thailand denied doing so. There were some border tensions between Myanmar and Thailand, but it never escalated into a conflict.
AFG is coded as an actor because the US and Georgia were fighting against al-Qaeda insurgenets in Georgia, and al-Qaeda was supported by Afghanistan
It's unclear if Russia is in conflict with Georgia also -- they could be on both sides of the conflict
There were other countries involved in the invasion of Iraq, but they played an insignificant role
Negotiations about North Korea's nuclear program stalled and neither side really won
Iran is considered to lose because they agreed to stop developing nuclear weapons, but it was still an agreement
Israel was actually fighting with Palestine (not a state), but since it struck a Palestinian military camp in Syria, it is considered to be in conflict with Syria
Neither side appears to have won this conflict
Burundi was also involved in the conflict since many of the rebel troops were supported by Burundi
